#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:0
msgid "Use Cases"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:5
msgid ""
"<span class=\"lead\">Open contracting data can be used in many different "
"ways: and each user's objectives affect the exact fields of data they need "
"to access.</span>"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:7
msgid ""
"In our consultations thus far with government, civil society, donors, "
"journalists, auditors, and the private sector, four primary use cases "
"emerged. These users are wishing to use open contracting data in order to:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:14
msgid ""
"We encourage all publishers to provide a common core of data about their "
"contracting processes that speaks to the prioritized demand requirements of "
"these use cases. The specification is also extensible, so that publishers "
"can further tailor their publication of contracting data to meet a wider "
"range of user needs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:16
msgid ""
"Demand requirements were prioritized based on their prevalence amongst use "
"cases as well as their feasibility of implementation (given our observations"
" of current 'supply side' publication practice). Demand requirements that "
"were not captured in the current specification have been identified and "
"noted for further consideration, or for publisher extension, at a later "
"date."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:0
msgid "Value for money in procurement"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:20
msgid ""
"<img src=\"../../../assets/icon_user.png\" width=\"150\" "
"align=\"right\"/>Open contracting data can help users to get good value for "
"money on the goods and services in the procurement process, and can also "
"help users to identify whether value for money has been achieved in "
"concluded contracts. These users are interested to analyze trends in prices "
"and supplier performance (in terms of quality and duration)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:22
msgid ""
"Comparable data using common codelists and the availability of unit prices "
"is particularly important for value for money use cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:0
msgid "Detecting fraud and corruption"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:26
msgid ""
"<img src=\"../../../assets/icon_user.png\" width=\"150\" "
"align=\"right\"/>All stakeholders (civil society, the private sector, "
"government and donors) have an interest in identifying and combating "
"corruption in public contracting. Open contracting data can be used to "
"scrutinize procurement documents and data for ‘red flags’ that might "
"indicate public monies are being mis-used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:28
msgid ""
"There are two main approaches to fraud and corruption monitoring. A ‘micro’ "
"approach closely scrutinizes individual procurements. A ‘systemic’ approach "
"looks for suspcious patterns, and makes links between datasets to map out "
"networks of funding, ownership and interests."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:30
msgid ""
"Linkable data using globally unique identifiers for companies are "
"particularly important for fraud and corruption detection use cases."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:0
msgid "Competing for public contracts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:34
msgid ""
"<img src=\"../../../assets/icon_user.png\" width=\"150\" "
"align=\"right\"/>Open contracting data can be used to track contracting "
"opportunities. It is a core principle of open contracting that information "
"should be made available at the early stages of a contracting process, "
"including clear information on opportunities to tender for public contracts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:36
msgid ""
"Information on past contracts can allow firms to identify likely upcoming "
"opportunities for re-contracting, and can support a more competitive "
"marketplace, as transparency creates a level playing field with information "
"on pricing, contract dates and key deliverables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:38
msgid ""
"Forward looking and timely information is particularly important for private"
" sector users, as well as being able to uniquely identify procuring "
"entities, geographic locations, sectors, and that which is being procured."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:0
msgid "Monitoring Service Delivery"
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:42
msgid ""
"<img src=\"../../../assets/icon_user.png\" width=\"150\" "
"align=\"right\"/>This user wants to ensure that public contracting is "
"delivering value to citizens in terms of quality of goods, works, and "
"services. This involves being able to link budgets and donor data to the "
"contracts and results. It also involves being able to verify whether results"
" are being delivered on the ground."
msgstr ""

#: ../../standard/docs/en/standard/use_cases.md:44
msgid ""
"Data concerning location and subcontracting is particularly useful for those"
" involved in contracting monitoring."
msgstr ""

